@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home";
}

<div class="row title-row">
    <div class="fill-screen" style="background-image: url(images/Banner/slider-4.jpg)">
        <div class="row-title">
            <h2>Welcome to Lake Creek Ranch</h2>
            <p>102 Acre subdivision near beautiful Troy, MT</p>
        </div>
        <div class="down-button">
            <a class="btn" href="#section-sales">
                <i class="fa fa-arrow-circle-down fa-4x"></i>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


<section id="section-sales" class="topmargin-lg">    
    <div class="heading-block center">
        <h2>Cabin Available For <span>Sale</span></h2>
        <span>65 Lakota Loop</span><br><span>See <a href="http://mymobile.flexmls.com/TracyNicely/listings/link/20170928165326388800000000" target="_blank"><span>MLS </span>Listing</a> for pricing and details.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="feature-box media-box">
                <div class="fbox-media">
                    <img src="~/images/homesite/homesite-8.jpg" alt="Why choose Us?">
                </div>
                <div class="fbox-desc">
                    <h3>Rustic Charm.<span class="subtitle">With Modern Conviences</span></h3>
                    <p>This 1630 square foot cabin sits on 3 acres. With a main level master suite, this 3 bedroom 2 1/2 bath rustic cabin has all the conviences of a modern home.  Stick frame with wood siding construction includes high end finish work, 2 story hand selected stone fireplace, and quartz countertops.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="feature-box media-box">
                <div class="fbox-media">
                    <img src="~/images/homesite/homesite-7.jpg" alt="Why choose Us?">
                </div>
                <div class="fbox-desc">
                    <h3>Spacious Back Porch<span class="subtitle">Beautiful Views of the Cabinet Mountains.</span></h3>
                    <p>This cabin includes a 400 square foot bonus room with roughed in bath and kitchen potential above the detached garage.  The back yard has been cleared and seeded for family fun and games. </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="feature-box media-box">
                <div class="fbox-media">
                    <img src="~/images/homesite/homesite-3.jpg" alt="Guest Cabin">
                </div>
                <div class="fbox-desc">
                    <h3>Guest Cabin<span class="subtitle">Authentic Amish Log Cabin</span></h3>
                    <p>A perfect place for your summer guests to relax in their own space. A 500+ square foot authentic Amish log cabin.  1 bedroom, 1 bath with a kitchenette and antique wood burning stove.  Includes washer and drier hook-ups.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="section-cabin-details" class="topmargin-lg">
    <div class="heading-block center">
        <h2>Cabin Details</h2>
        <span>65 Lakota Loop</span>
    </div>
</section>
<section id="section-about-us" class="topmargin-lg">
    <div class="heading-block center">
        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <span>Meet Doug and DeAnn Thomas</span>
    </div>

    <div class="container clearfix">

        <div class="col-md-6 bottommargin">
            <div class="team-image">
                <img src="images/team/team-1.jpg" alt="Doug and DeAnn">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6 bottommargin">
            <div class="team-desc">
                <div class="team-title"><span>Real Estate Developers</span></div>
                <div class="team-content">We fell in love with Montana while visiting friends in Troy over 10 years ago. At that time, we invested in this 102 acre parcel and have been developing it over the years.  We moved to Coeur d'Alene, Idaho  in the summer of 2015 with our youngest of 5 children.  We are originally from Auburn, California.  Our family has enjoyed many wonderful times in Northwest Montana, with its pristine lakes and rivers.  Many happy memories have been made boating on Bull Lake with friends and family.  You can play all day and practically have the whole lake to yourself! </div>

            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

</section>

<section id="section-property-details" class="topmargin-lg">
    <div class="heading-block center">
        <h2>The Property</h2>
        <span>Beautiful, wooded land with views of the cabinet mountains, abundant wildlife and endless possibilities for building your Montana dream home.  The property is ideal for horse and animal lovers alike.  Lots of level room for pastured horses and man's best friend.</span><br />
        <span>Phase 1 and 2 lots are now available.  11 lots ranging from 3 to 7 acres.  Contact us for more information</span>
    </div>
</section>

